definition:
ἀντ-απο-δίδωμι
 (ἀντί ἀποδίδωμι), [in LXX for שָׁלַם pi., גָּמַל, שׁוּב hi., etc. ;] 
to give back as an equivalent, recompense, requital (the ἀντί ex­pressing the idea of full, complete return; see Lft., Notes, 46); 
   (a) in favourable sense: Luk.14:14, Rom.11:35, 1Th.3:9; 
   (b) in unfavourable sense: Rom.12:19, 2Th.1:6, Heb.10:30.†
 (AS)
